Background

		Mr. Benjamin Howell Griswold, IV, also known as Ben, serves as the Chairman of Brown Investment Advisory & Trust Co. since March 2005. Mr. Griswold joined the firm in 2005. Previously, he served as the Head of U S Corporate Finance at Deutsche Bank AG. Mr. Griswold served as the Head of Endowment Board at Baltimore Symphony Orchestra Inc. He served as the Chairman of Deutsche Bank Alex. Brown Inc. and Deutsche Bank Securities Inc. Mr. Griswold served as the Chairman ... and Director of Alex Brown & Sons Inc. and Senior Chairman of BT Alex. Brown International. He served as Chairman of the board of the United Way of Central Maryland. Mr. Griswold served as a Partner since 1972, Chairman of the Board in 1987, Vice Chairman of the Board, since 1984 and Director since 1984 of Alex. Brown & Sons, where he began his career in 1967 and headed the research department, equity trading and equity divisions. He has been Presiding Director of Flowers Foods, Inc. since 2013 and its Independent Director since February 16, 2005. Mr. Griswold serves as Chairman of Brown Advisory Management, LLC. He has been a Member of Client Advisory Board of Deutsche Bank Trust Company Americas since January 25, 2007. Mr. Griswold serves as a Director of The Baltimore Life Insurance Company and Brown Advisory Management, LLC and a Member of Americas Advisory Board of Deutsche Bank AG. He serves as Emeritus Trustee of Johns Hopkins University, the Peabody Institute and Chairs the Baltimore Symphony Orchestra's Endowment Board. Mr. Griswold has been the Non-Executive Chairman of the Board of W. P. Carey Inc. since 2012 and Independent Director since 2006 and served as its a Lead Director since July 2010. He serves as an Independent Director of Signal Hill Capital Group LLC. Mr. Griswold is Member of Executive Council of Golub Capital LLC. He served as a Director of The Black & Decker Corporation from 2001 to March 12, 2010. Mr. Griswold served as a Director of Stanley Black & Decker, Inc. since March 12, 2010 until April 20, 2016. He served as a Director of the New York Stock Exchange and a Board Member of NYSE Holdings LLC. Mr. Griswold served as an artillery officer in the U.S. 7th Army in Germany. He has earned an M.B.A. degree from Harvard Business School in 1967 and an A.B. degree in Business Administration from the Princeton University in 1962.Read Full Background




