"The Brown Advisory offices are located by the harbor, where the clipper ships used to be, so just going to work will be very special for me," he said.The two segments he will run are the Brown Investment Advisory and Trust Company and Brown Advisory Securities. They have a total of 130 employees and manage investment assets of $9 billion, he said.Mr. Griswold, a Princeton graduate with an M.B.A. from Harvard, is a director at three companies: Black & Decker, Flowers Foods and the Baltimore Life Insurance Company.Volunteer work also keeps him busy, especially his role as a trustee of Johns Hopkins University in Baltimore. "I love to say about Johns Hopkins: They assume you don't have a job," he said in describing the workload there.Still, he finds time for his family: his wife, Wendy, eight children and three grandchildren. And he is passionate about steeplechase, owning a dozen horses on his Maryland farm, where competitions are held. "I also do some fox hunting," he said.   Robert Johnson Continue reading the main story






